main event: Two objects were tracked on radar near Portsmouth, New Hampshire on October 26, 1963. One object was confirmed by other radar stations, while the other object disappeared on radar. No visual sightings were reported.
interesting points: Object one was tracked at an altitude of 40-50,000 feet.
Object two disappeared on radar, but object one was confirmed by other radar stations.
The radar contact lasted for 10-12 minutes.
No visual sightings were reported, only the radar contacts.
The weather conditions at the time were not specified.
sighted object: two unidentified objects tracked on radar
